#Text=1 A method to manipulate flow behavior of a ducted fluid flow using very-small-scale effectors comp\u03C0smg the steps of . placmg arrays of very-small-scale effectors on ducted surfaces boundmg the ducted fluid flow ; and alte\u03C0ng a secondary flow structure in a boundary layer of the ducted fluid flow with said arrays of very- small-scale effectors on said ducted surfaces
#Text=2 . The method of Claim 1 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors are smaller than a duct boundary layer thickness of said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=3 . The method of Claim 1 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors are of an order of one-tenth said duct boundary layer thickness of said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=4 The method of Claim 1 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors are microfabricated elecrro- mechanical systems .

#Text=5 The method of Claim 1 , wherem said step of alte\u03C0ng said secondary flow structure comp\u03C0ses actively manipulatmg said arrays of very-small-scale effectors to mduce secondary flows withm the ducted fluid flow via active controls .
#Text=6 . The method of Claim 5 , wherem said secondary flows are co-rotatmg with the ducted fluid flow
#Text=7 The method of Claim 5 , wherem said secondary flows suppresses flow separation within the ducted fluid flow .

#Text=8 The method of Claim 5 , further comp\u03C0sing the steps of sensmg flow conditions withm the ducted fluid flow , with a flow sensor system ; and controlling said a\u03C0ay of very-small-scale effectors m response to said flow conditions , with a control system receivmg an mput from said flow sensor system , to produce a desired fluid flow withm said ducted fluid flow
#Text=9 . The method of Claim 8 , wherem said ducted fluid flow is within a low-observable duct
#Text=10 . The method of Claim 1 , wherem said ducted fluid flow is withm a low-observable duct
#Text=11 . The method of Claim 8 , wherem the ducted fluid flow is manipulated to reduce fatigue effects on downstream components located withm the ducted fluid flow
#Text=12 . The method of Claim 1 , wherem the ducted fluid flow is manipulated to reduce fatigue effects on downstream components located withm the ducted fluid flow .
#Text=13 . The method of Claim 11 , wherem said downstream components comprise an aircraft engine
#Text=14 . The method of Claim 13 , wherem the ducted fluid flow is manipulated to prevent said aircraft engine from stalling .

#Text=15 . A method to control flow behavior of a ducted fluid flow usmg very-small-scale effectors comprising the steps of : placing arrays of very-small-scale effectors on ducted surfaces boundmg the ducted fluid flow ; and altering a secondary flow structure m a boundary layer of the ducted fluid flow with said arrays of very- small-scale effectors on said ducted surfaces to control the flow behavior of the ducted fluid flow and wherein said very-small-scale effectors are smaller than a duct boundary layer thickness of said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=16 . The method of Claim 15 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors are of an order of one-tenth said duct boundary layer thickness of said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=17 . The method of Claim 15 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors are microfabricated electro- mechanical systems .

#Text=18 . The method of Claim 17 , wherem said step of alte\u03C0ng said second flow structure comprises actively manipulatmg said arrays of very-small-scale effectors induces secondary flows with the ducted fluid flow via active controls .
#Text=19 . The method of Claim 18 , wherem said secondary flows are co-rotating with the ducted fluid flow .
#Text=20 . The method of Claim 18 , wherem said secondary flows suppress flow separation within the ducted fluid flow

#Text=21 . The method of Claim 18 , further comp\u03C0smg the steps of : sensing flow conditions withm the ducted fluid flow , with a flow sensor system ; and controlling said a\u03C0ay of very-small-scale effectors in response to said flow conditions , with a control system receiving an input from said flow sensor system , to produce a desired fluid flow withm said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=22 . The method of Claim 21 , wherem said ducted fluid flow is withm a low-observable duct .
#Text=23 The method of Claim 21 , wherem the ducted fluid flow is manipulated to reduce fatigue effects on downstream components located within the ducted fluid flow .
#Text=24 . The method of Claim 23 , wherein said downstream components comprise an aircraft engine
#Text=25 The method of Claim 23 , wherein the ducted fluid flow is manipulated to prevent said aircraft engme from stalling .

#Text=26 A system to suppress flow separation of a fluid flow using very-small-scale effectors comp\u03C0smg : an arrays of very-small-scale effectors on surfaces bounding the fluid flow and wherem said very-small- scale effectors are microfab\u03C0cated electro-mechanical systems that are smaller than a boundary layer thickness of said fluid flow

#Text=27 . The system of Claim 26 further comprising : a control system coupled to said arrays operable to actively manipulate said a\u03C0ays on said surfaces to control the flow behavior of the fluid flow .
#Text=28 The system of Claim 26 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors are of an order of one-tenth said duct boundary layer thickness of said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=29 The system of Claim 26 , wherem said very-small-scale effectors induce secondary flows within the fluid flow via active control signals from said control system .

#Text=30 . The system of Claim 26 , further comprising : a sensor system operable to sense flow conditions withm the fluid flow and coupled to said control system wherein said control system is operable to manipulate said array of very-small-scale effectors in response to said flow conditions to produce a desired fluid flow withm said fluid flow .
#Text=31 The system of Claim 30 , wherem the fluid flow is a ducted fluid flow and wherem said surfaces are dueling surfaces
#Text=32 The system of Claim 31 , wherem said ducting surfaces comp\u03C0se a low-observable duct .

#Text=33 The system of Claim 31 , wherem said ducted fluid flow is actively manipulated by said array of very-small-scale effectors to reduce fatigue effects on downstream components located withm said ducted fluid flow .
#Text=34 . The system of Claim 33 , wherein said downstream components comprise an aircraft engine .
#Text=35 . The system of Claim 33 , wherein the ducted fluid flow is manipulated to improve operational performance of said downstream components .
#Text=36 . The system of Claim 33 , further comprising an external sensor system to sense physical conditions external to said ducted fluid flow which may effect said fluid flow .
